Comment: Aleksandr Alekhine was the first grandmaster to develop 1... N-KB3 as a viable defense to 1 P-K4. The Knight gets kicked a time or two in the early going but White doesn't develop any of his pieces either during the kicking, and the advanced Pawns could prove hard for White to defend. At least that's the theory...
